The '''grey-streaked honeyeater''' ('''''Ptiloprora perstriata'''''), also known as the '''black-backed honeyeater''', is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Meliphagidae]].  It is found in the [[New Guinea Highlands]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s.

